00:48:29,373 --> 00:48:30,803
Revolutionary millet wine

562
00:48:31,075 --> 00:48:32,095
It's called Malasun

563
00:48:32,576 --> 00:48:34,006
Age-old tradition with new sensation

564
00:48:34,378 --> 00:48:35,668
This is for you. Try it please

565
00:48:36,714 --> 00:48:38,764
He’s waiting for you upstairs

566
00:48:39,884 --> 00:48:41,024
Thank you

567
00:48:41,252 --> 00:48:42,012
Mr. Representative...

568
00:48:42,219 --> 00:48:44,829
I'm the only salesman in Hengchun

569
00:48:45,256 --> 00:48:47,185
I'm wondering if you can help me...

570
00:48:47,525 --> 00:48:48,665
..and introduce me to other hotels

571
00:48:49,126 --> 00:48:50,706
My boss wants this new product...

572
00:48:50,995 --> 00:48:53,395
...to be high-class

573
00:48:53,998 --> 00:48:56,048
Please. Do me the favor

574
00:48:56,734 --> 00:48:57,964
Baoli belongs to Checheng

575
00:48:58,202 --> 00:48:59,022
This is Hengchun here

576
00:48:59,470 --> 00:49:00,779
Why should I help you?

577
00:49:01,505 --> 00:49:03,175
Have some pride, young man

578
00:49:03,707 --> 00:49:05,926
Stop kissing someone's ass for money

579
00:49:15,553 --> 00:49:18,513
Yeah, not bad

580
00:49:19,290 --> 00:49:22,220
I've been watching them rehearsing

581
00:49:30,167 --> 00:49:32,156
Yeah, the first song will be ready this week

582
00:49:32,503 --> 00:49:34,963
The second one by this weekend

583
00:49:35,506 --> 00:49:37,145
The weather's gone mad and the sea is boiling

584
00:49:37,441 --> 00:49:39,401
That's why I want to seize the day

585
00:49:39,944 --> 00:49:42,663
Stop wasting time

586
00:49:43,113 --> 00:49:45,692
Be a skywalker...

587
00:49:46,116 --> 00:49:47,426
Stop...

588
00:49:47,718 --> 00:49:48,567
What?

589
00:49:49,153 --> 00:49:50,933
I'm adding something here

590
00:49:53,624 --> 00:49:58,194
Be a skywalker...

591
00:50:13,444 --> 00:50:18,514
Amen!

592
00:50:22,052 --> 00:50:23,952
All right, whatever. As you wish

593
00:50:24,722 --> 00:50:25,712
One more time!

594
00:50:27,424 --> 00:50:29,324
-When the sky is empty... -Wait...

595
00:50:29,660 --> 00:50:30,680
After that...

596
00:50:30,928 --> 00:50:32,388
...l'll try something cool. Come on!

597
00:50:33,831 --> 00:50:34,941
Hey!

598
00:50:36,133 --> 00:50:38,093
Can you try it after we do it once?

599
00:50:38,669 --> 00:50:39,719
It's been 3 days

600
00:50:40,504 --> 00:50:41,874
We haven't finish anything yet

601
00:50:42,373 --> 00:50:43,663
You, with the keyboard!

602
00:50:43,908 --> 00:50:44,868
Mind your tempo

603
00:50:45,442 --> 00:50:46,812
The bass guitar is lagging

604
00:50:47,545 --> 00:50:48,415
Drummer can’t stop criticizing

605
00:50:48,612 --> 00:50:49,842
What the hell do you want?

606
00:50:50,881 --> 00:50:52,841
What? Stop moaning!

607
00:50:53,417 --> 00:50:54,727
You look down upon us, don’t you?

608
00:50:55,319 --> 00:50:56,839
You're the best, all right?

609
00:50:57,254 --> 00:50:58,424
Only you can say anything

610
00:50:58,789 --> 00:50:59,489
What do you want?

611
00:50:59,657 --> 00:51:01,357
What? Wanna fight?

612
00:51:14,004 --> 00:51:15,614
I'd like to point out 3 things

613
00:51:16,173 --> 00:51:19,013
First, the keyboardist is too young

614
00:51:19,543 --> 00:51:20,973
. while the bass guitarist is too old

615
00:51:21,245 --> 00:51:23,615
We have to find someone else

616
00:51:24,281 --> 00:51:27,711
Second, you're a mess

617
00:51:28,252 --> 00:51:29,712
We should rehearse more often

618
00:51:31,388 --> 00:51:32,587
Third!

619
00:51:34,692 --> 00:51:37,712
They want you to write 2 songs

620
00:51:38,495 --> 00:51:41,565
But there’s only one now...

621
00:51:42,366 --> 00:51:45,116
.. written by you a long time ago

622
00:51:47,137 --> 00:51:49,767
But what matters is the other song

623
00:51:51,508 --> 00:51:52,678
Can you do it?

624
00:51:55,546 --> 00:51:56,596
Can you do it if l can’t?

625
00:51:57,548 --> 00:51:58,687
I'm not in charge here

626
00:52:06,991 --> 00:52:08,281
Ride to hell!

627
00:52:15,065 --> 00:52:16,025
Aga...

628
00:52:17,534 --> 00:52:19,114
When are you normally off duty?

629
00:52:21,572 --> 00:52:22,802
Around 5 o'clock

630
00:52:24,274 --> 00:52:25,354
5 o'clock?

631
00:52:26,043 --> 00:52:27,883
You're fast, aren't you?

632
00:52:29,913 --> 00:52:32,663
Put the mails inside the mailbox
to avoid them being stolen

633
00:52:33,283 --> 00:52:35,243
I've got complaints about losing mails

634
00:52:52,503 --> 00:52:53,373
Hey, girl!

635
00:52:54,738 --> 00:52:55,848
Who do you want?

636
00:52:56,106 --> 00:52:59,706
Excuse me...Is Aga here?

637
00:53:00,744 --> 00:53:02,914
He’s off to work. What do you want?

638
00:53:03,280 --> 00:53:04,300
He won't be back until late afternoon

639
00:53:06,917 --> 00:53:08,527
I'm the coordinator of the band

640
00:53:08,886 --> 00:53:11,106
This CD is for his reference

641
00:53:11,488 --> 00:53:13,328
Please give it to him

642
00:53:13,924 --> 00:53:17,294
So, you're that Japanese girl?

643
00:53:17,828 --> 00:53:19,668
Come on. Come in, please

644
00:53:19,997 --> 00:53:23,096
No, thanks. I'll write him a note

645
00:53:30,007 --> 00:53:31,347
Won't you come in and have a seat?

646
00:53:31,608 --> 00:53:32,308
No, thanks

647
00:53:34,411 --> 00:53:35,811
You're Japanese...

648
00:53:36,080 --> 00:53:37,569
...but you write well in Chinese

649
00:54:17,054 --> 00:54:18,224
I'm sorry. Are you all right?

650
00:54:18,455 --> 00:54:19,654
I didn’t mean to hurt you

651
00:54:20,023 --> 00:54:21,253
My betel nut...

652
00:54:22,693 --> 00:54:23,453
What is it?

653
00:54:23,627 --> 00:54:25,207
I'm fine

654
00:54:26,530 --> 00:54:27,460
Are you all right?

655
00:54:27,664 --> 00:54:28,974
I can't see

656
00:54:31,401 --> 00:54:33,571
Wipe them clean! I can’t see...

657
00:54:34,838 --> 00:54:36,268
Help him up

658
00:54:36,540 --> 00:54:37,800
My legs are fine

659
00:54:38,842 --> 00:54:39,922
Get on!

660
00:54:40,177 --> 00:54:41,167
Wipe them clean!

661
00:54:43,981 --> 00:54:45,561
Excuse me...well...

662
00:54:46,650 --> 00:54:47,940
Thank you

663
00:54:55,159 --> 00:54:56,909
What happened? Are his hands hurt?

664
00:55:00,531 --> 00:55:01,551
Damn!

665
00:55:02,566 --> 00:55:03,796
What happened to your nose?

666
00:55:04,034 --> 00:55:05,934
He’s hurt already
and you put an X on his nose?

667
00:55:06,303 --> 00:55:07,502
His wound is right here

668
00:55:07,738 --> 00:55:09,578
l have to avoid his eyes and nose tip

669
00:55:09,907 --> 00:55:10,727
What else can do?

670
00:55:13,277 --> 00:55:15,737
What are you laughing at? He’s in pain

671
00:56:07,865 --> 00:56:09,615
The staircase is too steep

672
00:56:24,047 --> 00:56:26,387
You really know how to play this?

673
00:56:26,783 --> 00:56:29,063
Can you do it?

674
00:56:35,525 --> 00:56:37,195
It's not what you're thinking!

675
00:56:43,867 --> 00:56:45,037
Aga!

676
00:56:46,236 --> 00:56:47,496
Aga...

677
00:56:53,944 --> 00:56:55,904
Please! Don’t tell anyone!

678
00:56:56,246 --> 00:56:58,386
He’s young and ignorant
Why don’t you help him?

679
00:56:58,749 --> 00:56:59,738
Don’t I have anything better to do?

680
00:57:00,150 --> 00:57:02,580
I'm old and limping
and you want me to help him?

681
00:57:03,086 --> 00:57:05,015
How many times have I told you?

682
00:57:05,355 --> 00:57:06,205
What if it’s notifying someone's...

683
00:57:06,423 --> 00:57:07,653
.. wedding, giving birth or death?

684
00:57:08,825 --> 00:57:10,495
We have phones. Who writes letters anymore?

685
00:57:10,794 --> 00:57:11,554
Damn you!

686
00:57:12,262 --> 00:57:13,572
Are you working for the post office
or the phone company?

687
00:57:14,831 --> 00:57:16,411
Old Mao, don’t tell anyone please

688
00:57:16,700 --> 00:57:17,370
Come on. I don’t need money

689
00:57:17,534 --> 00:57:18,384
Buy whatever you like with it

690
00:57:18,568 --> 00:57:19,498
I like playing music

691
00:57:19,703 --> 00:57:21,253
Buy a new instrument then

692
00:57:21,538 --> 00:57:22,588
Who am I playing for?

693
00:57:22,839 --> 00:57:23,979
Who wants to listen to...

694
00:57:24,207 --> 00:57:25,517
...us old people playing?

695
00:57:25,876 --> 00:57:26,986
The newspaper says I’m a gem

696
00:57:27,277 --> 00:57:29,297
Who gives a damn?

697
00:57:29,880 --> 00:57:31,400
If 'm a gem, I should go out and show them...

698
00:57:31,715 --> 00:57:33,325
.. instead of staying at home

699
00:57:45,095 --> 00:57:45,825
All right...

700
00:57:45,996 --> 00:57:48,456
Only hundreds of them
They won't give you so hard a time

701
00:57:49,032 --> 00:57:51,582
l heard someone got in jail
for opening private letters

702
00:57:52,803 --> 00:57:54,413
I told you it’s not that!

703
00:57:54,705 --> 00:57:55,575
What is it then?

704
00:57:56,273 --> 00:57:57,563
Porno?

705
00:57:58,442 --> 00:57:59,702
Yeah, yeah...

706
00:58:04,414 --> 00:58:05,814
How I wish a storm would come now...

707
00:58:06,717 --> 00:58:11,227
...and drown me in the ocean
between Taiwan and Japan

708
00:58:13,290 --> 00:58:18,360
Then I won't have to be
responsible for my cowardice

709
00:58:21,198 --> 00:58:22,308
Tomoko...

710
00:58:23,467 --> 00:58:25,247
I've been sailing for several days

711
00:58:26,503 --> 00:58:28,903
The weeps brought by the sea wind

712
00:58:30,707 --> 00:58:33,426
age me already

713
00:58:34,845 --> 00:58:36,575
I don’t want to leave the deck

714
00:58:37,714 --> 00:58:39,084
or go to bed

715
00:58:40,784 --> 00:58:43,034
I've made up my mind

716
00:58:43,754 --> 00:58:45,804
Once ! land...

717
00:58:46,156 --> 00:58:48,176
..I'll no longer see the ocean

718
00:58:50,327 --> 00:58:54,837
Sea wind, why do you always bring the weeps?

719
00:58:56,666 --> 00:59:00,356
They weep for being in love,
for marrying someone

720
00:59:00,971 --> 00:59:03,371
or giving birth

721
00:59:03,774 --> 00:59:09,754
l weep when I think of you
marrying someone else

722
00:59:10,647 --> 00:59:14,107
But the sea wind dries my tears...

723
00:59:15,485 --> 00:59:17,565
...before they drop

724
00:59:18,255 --> 00:59:23,205
I can’t cry any tear, which ages me even more

725
00:59:25,362 --> 00:59:26,942
Curse the wind!

726
00:59:27,964 --> 00:59:29,484
Curse the moonlight!

727
00:59:31,535 --> 00:59:33,234
Curse the seal

728
01:00:03,867 --> 01:00:05,597
I told you already!

729
01:00:06,203 --> 01:00:07,663
The bass guitarist was too old

730
01:00:08,071 --> 01:00:09,941
Now you have someone even older

731
01:00:10,574 --> 01:00:12,384
It was not me who asked him here

732
01:00:12,709 --> 01:00:14,049
I'm not in charge here

733
01:00:14,344 --> 01:00:15,484
You're not in charge?

734
01:00:17,314 --> 01:00:22,234
All right, I'll see
how you're going to sing on stage

735
01:00:27,090 --> 01:00:28,700
I love my girl

736
01:00:29,259 --> 01:00:32,069
I love you so much

737
01:00:32,863 --> 01:00:35,763
When we were in the park...

738
01:00:36,533 --> 01:00:39,113
...do you know what happened?

739
01:00:40,036 --> 01:00:42,966
l saw the moonlight...

740
01:00:46,776 --> 01:00:48,265
You...

741
01:00:49,079 --> 01:00:51,829
You really want him
to use that as a bass guitar?

742
01:00:53,750 --> 01:00:56,620
I bet that old man...

743
01:00:58,655 --> 01:01:02,285
...never touched a bass guitar

744
01:01:04,127 --> 01:01:06,877
Our Japanese singer will be here soon

745
01:01:07,831 --> 01:01:08,941
What can we do now?

746
01:01:09,633 --> 01:01:11,303
What about your other song?

747
01:01:11,835 --> 01:01:13,565
l haven’t seen anything!

748
01:01:14,671 --> 01:01:16,310
Have you listened to the CD I gave you?

749
01:01:22,279 --> 01:01:24,679
Look at him!

750
01:01:25,282 --> 01:01:27,892
Don’t tell me writing songs
is not your job

751
01:01:30,787 --> 01:01:31,957
What are you doing?

752
01:01:34,925 --> 01:01:36,125
Look!

753
01:01:36,793 --> 01:01:37,903
It's salt!

754
01:01:38,662 --> 01:01:41,881
He spent his time at the beach

755
01:01:43,500 --> 01:01:44,550
You've been late everyday

756
01:01:44,834 --> 01:01:47,354
I thought you were busy writing songs

757
01:01:48,071 --> 01:01:50,181
Now I know that you were at the beach

758
01:01:53,376 --> 01:01:55,716
How can you be so mean?

759
01:01:56,913 --> 01:01:58,223
I quit!

760
01:01:59,316 --> 01:02:00,895
Get out of my way!

761
01:02:05,655 --> 01:02:07,525
Why didn’t you say anything?

762
01:02:09,025 --> 01:02:11,045
Do you understand anything she said?

763
01:02:17,033 --> 01:02:18,493
Wow! The Japanese eats everything!

764
01:02:18,802 --> 01:02:21,962
l see the moonlight sprinkling

765
01:02:22,505 --> 01:02:24,875
l have something to tell you

766
01:02:25,842 --> 01:02:29,502
Please think about it, girl...

767
01:02:30,080 --> 01:02:30,750
What are you doing?

768
01:02:30,914 --> 01:02:32,644
Play this

769
01:02:32,949 --> 01:02:34,259
How do you play this thing?

770
01:03:45,255 --> 01:03:47,305
Hey! Are you leaving?

771
01:03:50,093 --> 01:03:52,582
Hey! Japanese girl!

772
01:03:53,129 --> 01:03:55,618
Your job is not done. Why are you leaving?

773
01:04:12,716 --> 01:04:15,645
Miss Tomoko, what's wrong with you?

774
01:04:16,152 --> 01:04:17,202
Miss Tomoko!

775
01:04:19,589 --> 01:04:20,788
Miss Tomoko...

776
01:04:21,024 --> 01:04:24,013
The grandson of my younger brother
is getting married today

777
01:04:24,494 --> 01:04:26,924
We have the reception this evening

778
01:04:27,330 --> 01:04:28,759
Please come and enjoy with us

779
01:04:29,032 --> 01:04:30,872
We'll be waiting for you

780
01:04:38,375 --> 01:04:39,805
Congratulations

781
01:04:43,780 --> 01:04:45,240
I'm the bass guitarist of the band

782
01:04:45,548 --> 01:04:47,067
I want to practice a little

783
01:05:11,574 --> 01:05:13,154
Look, Mr. Representative!

784
01:05:15,578 --> 01:05:17,038
This Hakka is so diligent

785
01:05:17,814 --> 01:05:19,513
He works day in and day out

786
01:05:20,617 --> 01:05:22,487
Diligence is the only strategy he knows

787
01:05:23,153 --> 01:05:24,263
The bottles of wine he’s sold today...

788
01:05:24,487 --> 01:05:26,187
...are more than the mails at Aga’s

789
01:05:26,856 --> 01:05:27,846
Shit!

790
01:05:28,091 --> 01:05:29,901
Nothing...

791
01:05:54,484 --> 01:05:56,004
Hey! Malasun!

792
01:06:18,708 --> 01:06:20,928
Chateau Hotel. May I help you?

793
01:06:22,445 --> 01:06:23,525
60 bottles?

794
01:06:26,082 --> 01:06:29,152
OK...Thank you. Bye

795
01:06:47,537 --> 01:06:48,327
Let me show you one more time

796
01:06:48,505 --> 01:06:49,645
Why can’t I do it right?

797
01:06:49,873 --> 01:06:50,743
What can I do?

798
01:06:52,575 --> 01:06:53,444
Malasun!

799
01:06:54,777 --> 01:06:55,707
What the hell?

800
01:06:55,912 --> 01:06:57,022
Let me show you. It’s...

801
01:06:57,447 --> 01:06:59,257
Malasun! You hit the jackpot!

802
01:06:59,582 --> 01:07:00,721
Mr. Representative called...

803
01:07:00,950 --> 01:07:02,120
...and asked for 60 bottles of wine

804
01:07:02,385 --> 01:07:03,315
For the wedding reception

805
01:07:03,553 --> 01:07:04,752
60...

806
01:07:07,323 --> 01:07:08,343
I'm sorry...

807
01:07:22,772 --> 01:07:25,292
60! 60 bottles...

808
01:07:25,708 --> 01:07:28,428
Malasun, you know Mr. Representative well?

809
01:07:30,780 --> 01:07:32,620
Please give this old man a chance

810
01:07:32,949 --> 01:07:35,059
Don’t tell him you can play, please

811
01:07:36,286 --> 01:07:38,066
Malasun! Hi, everyone!

812
01:07:38,421 --> 01:07:39,181
It's on Mr. Representative

813
01:07:39,355 --> 01:07:40,995
Our company’s new product Malasun millet wine

814
01:07:41,291 --> 01:07:42,841
Aga!

815
01:07:48,498 --> 01:07:50,048
Come on...Bon appetit!

816
01:07:52,135 --> 01:07:53,065
Miss Tomoko...

817
01:07:53,303 --> 01:07:54,502
This is Aga’s mother

818
01:07:55,071 --> 01:07:57,321
I've seen her. She visited us once

819
01:07:58,374 --> 01:07:59,394
Sit there!

820
01:08:15,858 --> 01:08:16,908
Harder!

821
01:08:17,627 --> 01:08:20,177
Next! Mr. Chen Kuang-hui

822
01:08:20,630 --> 01:08:22,150
Here ] am! I’m Chen Kuang-hui

823
01:08:23,366 --> 01:08:25,856
Dad, my head aches! Stop!

824
01:08:26,301 --> 01:08:27,612
All right!

825
01:08:27,870 --> 01:08:29,040
I don’t need help!

826
01:08:32,408 --> 01:08:34,018
Idiot!

827
01:08:59,702 --> 01:09:01,222
Wow! You really can drink!

828
01:09:18,121 --> 01:09:20,581
Why are you dressed like this?

829
01:09:20,990 --> 01:09:22,830
I don’t know. Well...

830
01:09:23,158 --> 01:09:24,268
Sit there...

831
01:09:27,863 --> 01:09:28,853
There’s no seat here

832
01:09:29,064 --> 01:09:30,794
I'll... sit there instead

833
01:09:32,734 --> 01:09:33,724
Hi, Ma’am

834
01:09:35,470 --> 01:09:37,020
Why are you dressed like this?

835
01:09:38,006 --> 01:09:39,676
Uncle Frog, you’re handsome!

836
01:09:40,009 --> 01:09:41,618
Thank you, Mr. Lin

837
01:09:41,911 --> 01:09:43,640
You're so cute!

838
01:09:44,247 --> 01:09:47,267
Stop, you chicken! I'll get you!

839
01:09:49,385 --> 01:09:51,055
Go on...Cheer for Daddy

840
01:09:51,787 --> 01:09:53,277
