My head ached badly earlier today

935
01:19:04,873 --> 01:19:06,623
I hate this thick fog

936
01:19:07,176 --> 01:19:09,806
It blocked my sight during the day

937
01:19:11,213 --> 01:19:14,023
But the stars are beautiful

938
01:19:15,784 --> 01:19:19,853
Remember when you were in 7th grade...

939
01:19:21,257 --> 01:19:24,217
you challenged my lunar eclipse theory

940
01:19:24,693 --> 01:19:27,593
...with the myth of Moon being eaten?

941
01:19:29,531 --> 01:19:32,021
I'll tell you another scientific truth

942
01:19:33,535 --> 01:19:36,144
Do you know the stars we see now...

943
01:19:36,572 --> 01:19:38,622
...are lights reflected...

944
01:19:39,008 --> 01:19:40,468
...from billions of light-years away?

945
01:19:42,211 --> 01:19:46,901
Wow! Billions of light-years away!

946
01:19:48,050 --> 01:19:50,220
And we haven't seen them until now

947
01:19:51,820 --> 01:19:54,599
In billions of light-years...

948
01:19:55,090 --> 01:19:56,900
...what will Taiwan and Japan become of?

949
01:19:58,761 --> 01:20:01,481
Mountains and seas will still be there

950
01:20:03,065 --> 01:20:04,794
But the people will be gone

951
01:20:07,670 --> 01:20:10,480
l want to take another glimpse at the sky

952
01:20:12,574 --> 01:20:14,094
In this changeable world...

953
01:20:15,377 --> 01:20:16,987
...l want to see what eternity is

954
01:20:21,550 --> 01:20:24,540
I met a school of grey mullet
heading to Taiwan for the winter

955
01:20:26,655 --> 01:20:29,344
I trust my love to you to one of them

956
01:20:30,793 --> 01:20:34,893
May your fisherman father catch it

957
01:20:36,465 --> 01:20:40,185
Tomoko, though it tastes bad...

958
01:20:41,904 --> 01:20:43,514
... you have to try it anyway

959
01:20:44,707 --> 01:20:46,607
You'll understand...

960
01:20:47,676 --> 01:20:49,576
...that I didn’t mean to leave you

961
01:20:51,814 --> 01:20:55,684
I'm moaning on the deck at night...

962
01:20:57,786 --> 01:21:02,036
...that I didn’t mean to leave you

963
01:21:53,509 --> 01:21:55,679
You really expect anything from us?

964
01:22:04,720 --> 01:22:06,210
But after 15 years...

965
01:22:07,956 --> 01:22:09,736
...[ fail after all

966
01:22:13,228 --> 01:22:14,658
Though I’m not really that bad

967
01:22:46,295 --> 01:22:50,075
A new day dawns, but who cares?

968
01:22:51,834 --> 01:22:55,464
Sunlight only brings thick mist anyway

969
01:22:57,339 --> 01:22:59,299
I saw before dawn...

970
01:23:00,275 --> 01:23:02,855
...the aged you from the future...

971
01:23:04,279 --> 01:23:07,059
...and the aged me from the future

972
01:23:08,550 --> 01:23:12,120
The morning mist covers
my wrinkles on the forehead

973
01:23:13,021 --> 01:23:16,010
The sun scorches your black hair

974
01:23:17,626 --> 01:23:21,756
I've lost you completely

975
01:23:23,031 --> 01:23:24,401
Tomoko...

976
01:23:24,967 --> 01:23:26,866
Please forgive the cowardly me

977
01:24:12,714 --> 01:24:14,084
You...

978
01:24:15,050 --> 01:24:17,160
Those letters are very important

979
01:24:18,554 --> 01:24:19,634
You have to give them to that girl...

980
01:24:20,522 --> 01:24:22,892
... whatever it takes

981
01:24:47,082 --> 01:24:49,102
Oh, Jeez!

982
01:24:49,751 --> 01:24:51,711
Who did this?

983
01:25:14,076 --> 01:25:16,266
You idiot! You'll be put into jail!

984
01:25:17,145 --> 01:25:19,365
I told you to return the mail
but you opened it instead?

985
01:25:23,285 --> 01:25:25,625
Cape No.7, Hengchun

986
01:25:31,793 --> 01:25:33,543
Kojima Tomoko?

987
01:25:34,296 --> 01:25:36,256
I don’t remember this person

988
01:25:36,632 --> 01:25:38,802
We're about the same age if she’s still alive

989
01:25:46,541 --> 01:25:48,561
It's 16 degrees Celsius here...

990
01:25:48,910 --> 01:25:52,540
... with a 12-knot wind
above the 97-meter-deep sea

991
01:25:53,915 --> 01:25:56,815
I've seen a couple of sea birds

992
01:25:58,220 --> 01:26:00,330
We're landing tomorrow night

993
01:26:01,356 --> 01:26:02,556
Tomoko...

994
01:26:03,425 --> 01:26:05,735
I left you all my photos taken in Taiwan

995
01:26:07,062 --> 01:26:09,022
I gave them to your mother

996
01:26:09,998 --> 01:26:12,748
But I took one of them with me

997
01:26:14,136 --> 01:26:16,686
It's you playing at the beach

998
01:26:18,040 --> 01:26:21,670
The sea in the photo is so calm...

999
01:26:22,744 --> 01:26:26,344
...and your smiles fascinate me

1000
01:26:28,316 --> 01:26:30,246
Whoever your new lover will be...

1001
01:26:31,119 --> 01:26:33,398
...he can’t be good enough for you

1002
01:26:35,290 --> 01:26:39,100
I thought I packed all my beautiful memories

1003
01:26:40,295 --> 01:26:42,485
Now I realize that alll can take away
is emptiness

1004
01:26:43,231 --> 01:26:46,251
l really miss you!

1005
01:26:47,969 --> 01:26:49,959
Wow! Rainbow!

1006
01:27:00,449 --> 01:27:02,259
May the rainbow bridge the two ends of ocean

1007
01:27:02,884 --> 01:27:06,194
...and bridge you and me

1008
01:27:26,675 --> 01:27:31,505
When sunshine returns

1009
01:27:32,414 --> 01:27:36,514
To the rainy southern country

1010
01:27:37,486 --> 01:27:40,036
lll try to finish

1011
01:27:41,823 --> 01:27:47,623
The love story in the past

1012
01:27:48,630 --> 01:27:51,440
When sunshine...

1013
01:27:56,371 --> 01:27:58,651
So many strings. I can’t do it right

1014
01:27:59,374 --> 01:28:00,634
It's a love song!

1015
01:28:01,743 --> 01:28:03,443
It's easy. Only a few chords

1016
01:28:03,745 --> 01:28:04,945
Come on!

1017
01:28:07,482 --> 01:28:10,142
Let me tell you something
Come earlier to practice tomorrow

1018
01:28:10,585 --> 01:28:11,315
All right...

1019
01:28:11,486 --> 01:28:13,006
I never use these two strings

1020
01:28:13,455 --> 01:28:14,745
Can I cut them off?

1021
01:28:14,990 --> 01:28:16,450
No, you can’t!

1022
01:28:16,758 --> 01:28:18,657
Say it nicely. Why did you shout?

1023
01:28:44,486 --> 01:28:46,976
Have you found that girl?

1024
01:28:47,422 --> 01:28:49,382
I tried, but didn’t find her

1025
01:28:50,125 --> 01:28:51,115
I'll try harder

1026
01:28:54,663 --> 01:28:55,652
The lyrics...

1027
01:28:57,833 --> 01:28:59,473
I know. I'll revise them

1028
01:29:00,969 --> 01:29:03,109
So...l have to go

1029
01:29:12,447 --> 01:29:13,847
I need to turn off the lights

1030
01:29:15,116 --> 01:29:17,256
Il do it

1031
01:29:24,526 --> 01:29:26,306
All right, it’s up to you guys

1032
01:29:27,729 --> 01:29:30,159
Yeah, I think he can do it well

1033
01:29:31,066 --> 01:29:32,266
I think so too

1034
01:29:32,834 --> 01:29:33,704
Damn!

1035
01:29:34,836 --> 01:29:37,146
You were so quick to answer

1036
01:29:37,906 --> 01:29:38,926
I'm senile!

1037
01:29:39,174 --> 01:29:41,804
You hurt my feelings

1038
01:29:43,445 --> 01:29:45,144
It's you who brought him here, not us

1039
01:29:45,447 --> 01:29:47,437
Yeah! We don’t even know him

1040
01:29:49,117 --> 01:29:50,847
Never mind me, Old Mao

1041
01:29:51,152 --> 01:29:53,552
Come on! I know what you want

1042
01:29:54,856 --> 01:29:56,196
You're cocky only because
you can play the bass guitar?

1043
01:30:00,528 --> 01:30:02,138
Why can’t we have two bass guitarists?

1044
01:30:06,735 --> 01:30:08,464
Any instrument is all right for me

1045
01:30:08,770 --> 01:30:09,760
l have to be on stage

1046
01:30:10,906 --> 01:30:12,076
Damn! They say I’m a gem!

1047
01:30:45,907 --> 01:30:49,657
Tomoko, I’ve landed safely

1048
01:30:51,379 --> 01:30:53,019
After the seven-day voyage...

1049
01:30:53,982 --> 01:30:57,522
...[ finally step on my homeland

1050
01:30:58,987 --> 01:31:01,127
But I miss the sea already

1051
01:31:03,158 --> 01:31:04,388
Why is the sea standing for...

1052
01:31:04,626 --> 01:31:07,086
...the two extremes of hope and death?

1053
01:31:08,697 --> 01:31:12,037
This is my last letter to you

1054
01:31:12,567 --> 01:31:14,237
I'll mail them later

1055
01:31:15,837 --> 01:31:18,297
This sea can’t tolerate love

1056
01:31:18,707 --> 01:31:21,517
At least it can tolerate lovesickness

1057
01:31:23,078 --> 01:31:26,918
Tomoko, you must receive my lovesickness

1058
01:31:28,283 --> 01:31:31,913
So that you'll forgive me a little bit

1059
01:31:33,355 --> 01:31:36,075
I'll bury you in my heart forever

1060
01:31:36,958 --> 01:31:39,008
Even when I'm getting married...

1061
01:31:39,527 --> 01:31:41,927
...or at some turning points of life...

1062
01:31:42,530 --> 01:31:44,519
...’m bound to think of you

1063
01:31:45,633 --> 01:31:48,093
The girl who ran away from home...

1064
01:31:48,503 --> 01:31:52,313
... Standing alone in the crowd...

1065
01:31:53,908 --> 01:31:55,868
... wearing the white hat...

1066
01:31:56,211 --> 01:31:57,881
... which you'd worked so hard to buy

1067
01:31:58,913 --> 01:32:02,723
You wanted me to recognize you
in the crowd, didn’t you?

1068
01:32:05,754 --> 01:32:10,264
Il saw you...1 saw you...

1069
01:32:12,327 --> 01:32:15,577
You were standing there silently

1070
01:32:16,131 --> 01:32:18,301
It's an old address. Anyone knows?

1071
01:32:21,803 --> 01:32:23,793
You're like the July sun

1072
01:32:25,273 --> 01:32:27,203
I dare not glimpse at you any longer

1073
01:32:30,378 --> 01:32:34,888
l saw you standing there silently

1074
01:32:36,818 --> 01:32:40,478
You lit up my chilled heart

1075
01:32:41,990 --> 01:32:43,740
l was sad, but had to hide my feelings

1076
01:32:44,859 --> 01:32:50,129
I didn’t speak anything

1077
01:32:51,699 --> 01:32:54,098
I know that my lovesickness...

1078
01:32:54,502 --> 01:32:57,112
...1S like the shadow under the sun...

1079
01:32:57,539 --> 01:33:01,169
... chased by me and chasing me...

1080
01:33:01,743 --> 01:33:04,023
...for the eternity

1081
01:33:24,199 --> 01:33:26,039
Why are you so sad?

1082
01:33:26,968 --> 01:33:29,628
Because of love? Of work?

1083
01:33:30,271 --> 01:33:34,050
Or is it because of us?

1084
01:33:37,979 --> 01:33:42,639
I'm afraid it'll still be raining tomorrow

1085
01:33:46,621 --> 01:33:47,881
Miss Tomoko...

1086
01:33:49,124 --> 01:33:51,784
Aren’t you expecting the rainbow?

1087
01:34:00,468 --> 01:34:01,638
Tomoko...

1088
01:34:02,537 --> 01:34:06,197
l wrote my guiltiness in my last letter...

1089
01:34:07,742 --> 01:34:10,762
...to show my apology to you

1090
01:34:12,447 --> 01:34:16,257
That's how I can forgive myself

1091
01:34:25,293 --> 01:34:27,253
Hey, you two!

1092
01:34:27,629 --> 01:34:29,119
No singing for you tomorrow on stage
Can you live with that?

1093
01:34:31,833 --> 01:34:33,673
l was sleepless last night, thinking

1094
01:34:34,369 --> 01:34:35,709
I've played yukin for more than 50 years

1095
01:34:36,004 --> 01:34:37,614
I'll be on stage for the first time
tomorrow and I'll be shaking this?

1096
01:34:39,007 --> 01:34:40,297
Hey, you!

1097
01:34:40,842 --> 01:34:42,302
You can sing very well

1098
01:34:42,911 --> 01:34:43,901
Don’t you want to sing on stage?

1099
01:34:44,112 --> 01:34:44,782
I think...

1100
01:34:44,946 --> 01:34:46,616
Shut up! No one asks you anything

1101
01:35:04,566 --> 01:35:06,266
Hey, slam-dunker...

1102
01:35:07,569 --> 01:35:09,089
Red hair is not trendy now

1103
01:35:15,076 --> 01:35:17,006
Aga is home revising the lyrics

1104
01:35:17,612 --> 01:35:18,902
He asked us to rehearse without him

1105
01:35:24,118 --> 01:35:26,488
Today, 1 bought something
for each of you at the airport

1106
01:35:27,455 --> 01:35:30,115
Dada, this is Ancestors’ Eyes...

1107
01:35:30,825 --> 01:35:32,724
...to protect your health

1108
01:35:33,061 --> 01:35:33,731
Thank you

1109
01:35:36,130 --> 01:35:37,440
Malasun!

1110
01:35:39,000 --> 01:35:40,290
This is Bead of Butterfly Pupa...

1111
01:35:40,702 --> 01:35:42,402
...to bring you fortune...

1112
01:35:42,770 --> 01:35:44,500
